The paper deals with the problem of knowledge fusion, which involves identifying true subject-predicate-object triples extracted by multiple information extractors from multiple information sources. This problem is related to several areas of computer science, including databases (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of state-of-the-art data fusion techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and data mining. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
